turning back one's life
The rest of your life is shorter than the rest of your life so far, but still, if you don't keep learning for the future, even the rest of your life will soon be rotten!

The model of hoarding in the first half of life and then living the second half while spewing it out is not viable.
　Unlike money, knowledge is a "fungible" thing.
　Like raw vegetables that are difficult to save.

